HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1212
By Martin G
A RESOLUTION to recognize Becky Kirk on the occasion of her
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
years of public service; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable person is Becky Kirk, who, having admirably served the
citizens of Hamilton County in the Department of Human Services for nearly four decades, is
taking a much-deserved retirement this year; and
WHEREAS, a graduate of Hixson High School and the University of Tennessee at
Chattanooga, Ms. Kirk is a certified fraud examiner and has served the State of Tennessee with
dedication, organization, and professionalism; and
WHEREAS, Becky Kirk has served as a program monitor and assisted with programs
such as the Child and Adult Care Food Program for citizens with food insecurities; and
WHEREAS, in addition to her outstanding leadership and public service, Ms. Kirk is a
loving wife, mother of two successful children, and grandmother to several wonderful
grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, Becky Kirk exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community
that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout her tenure, Ms. Kirk has distinguished herself as a public-
spirited citizen of the highest order, winning the respect and admiration of her colleagues and
the people she has so ably served; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
HJR1212
016301
- 1 -

CONCURRING, that we extend to Becky Kirk our heartfelt wishes for a happy and fulfilling
retirement and every continued success in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
